│ cause a discrepancy.\n\nIf `X` is `-inf`, the original code  │
│ behaves as follows:\n1.  `%cmp1 = fcmp ogt float -inf, 0.0`  │
│ evaluates to `false`.\n2.  `%add = fadd ninf float -inf,     │
