│ 1.0` evaluates to `1.0`.\n\nThe final result is the same     │
│ (`1.0`), but the intermediate values and potential for       │
│ `poison` are different. The `alive2` log correctly           │
│ identifies that the transformation is illegal because it can │
│ introduce `poison` where none existed. The transformation    │
│ `select(C, X+K, K) -> max(X,0)+K` is not sound if `X+K` can  │
│ produce `poison` (due to `ninf`) while the `select` would    │
│ have chosen the other, safe path.\n\n### 2. Analyzing        │
