│ Builder.CreateFAdd(createSelect(Cond, X, K), K);\n           │
│ }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n```\n\nThe proposed edit is to add   │
│ `if (Add->hasNoFMF())` around the `Builder.CreateFAdd` call. │
│ This ensures that the transformation is only applied when    │
│ the addition does not have any fast-math flags, preserving   │
│ the original semantics.\n\n### 5. Conclusion\n\nThe issue is │
│ a classic fast-math miscompilation where a transformation,   │
│ valid under standard floating-point rules, becomes incorrect │
